"{\"uid\": \"cyclingnews.com-features-the-defining-moments-of-the-2024-season-olympic-golds-a-triple-crown-and-records-smashed\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Cyclingnews looks back on the biggest victories and most defining moments of the 2024 road season  When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"-  The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 204, \"to\": 309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now subscribed  Your newsletter sign-up was successful  The 2024 season was one for the history books, with records broken, nail-biting storylines written, and new Olympic champions crowned.\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some Grand Tours went right down to the wire, while others were already tied up by the second week - such was the standout strength of their victors.\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 660, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alongside the victories, record-breakers, and history-makers, there were also season-defining moments that sprung from crashes.\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A few notable incidents shaped the campaigns of some of the peloton's key protagonists.\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To give each of these moments from the road their fair share of the limelight, we refrained from including highlights from other disciplines, such as gravel and mountain biking.\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, we can not not mentionPauline Ferrand-Pr\\u00e9vot's stunning women's cross-country mountain bike goldon her fourth and final attempt at the event, so tooTom Pidcock's breathtaking comebackin the men's event to defend his gold medal.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1294, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While in the world of gravel, the exhilarating World Championships in Belgium sawMarianne VosandMathieu van der Poelwin world titles in yet another discipline.\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1366, \"end\": 1373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999981355359, \"rank\": 1.8639482880089217e-09, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back to the tarmac though, and we have whittled a long list down to just 12 key moments from the 2024 road cycling season.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biniam Girmaymade history as the first Black African to win a stage at the Tour de Francewhen he stormed across the stage 3 finish line in Torino.\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1622, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0722654227359145e-37, \"text\": \"Black African\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1722, \"end\": 1728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\", \"score\": 0.9999999999636202, \"rank\": 3.662218629828849e-11, \"text\": \"Torino\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His hometown fans back in Eritrea also had double the reason to celebrateas he captured his nation's first-ever Tour stage win in the process.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1872, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1756, \"end\": 1763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eritrea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6416096363034404e-29, \"text\": \"Eritrea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eritrea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eritrea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 230.9-kilometre stage from Piacenza ended with Girmay blasting up close to the barriers on the right-hand side to win ahead of Fernando Gaviria (Movistar) and Arnaud De Lie (Lotto Dstny), taking the early lead in the green points classification.\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 2123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piacenza_Calcio_1919\", \"score\": 0.9019673634382078, \"rank\": 0.1086875651341423, \"text\": \"Piacenza\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piacenza_Calcio_1919\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piacenza_Calcio_1919\"}, {\"begin\": 2005, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fernando_Gaviria\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fernando Gaviria\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fernando_Gaviria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fernando_Gaviria\"}, {\"begin\": 2023, \"end\": 2031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Movistar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7825121793945635e-56, \"text\": \"Movistar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Movistar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Movistar\"}, {\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arnaud_de_Lie\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arnaud De Lie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arnaud_de_Lie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arnaud_de_Lie\"}, {\"begin\": 2052, \"end\": 2057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottery\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0168029796867775e-23, \"text\": \"Lotto\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lottery\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He captured another win on the 183.4km stage 8 from Semur-en-Auxois to Colombey-les-Deux-Eglises ahead ofJasper Philipsen(Alpecin-Deceuninck) and De Lie.\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2177, \"end\": 2192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Semur-en-Auxois\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Semur-en-Auxois\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Semur-en-Auxois\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Semur-en-Auxois\"}, {\"begin\": 2196, \"end\": 2221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colombey-les-Deux-\\u00c9glises\", \"score\": 0.9817096892888861, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Colombey-les-Deux-Eglises\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colombey-les-Deux-\\u00c9glises\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colombey-les-Deux-\\u00c9glises\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won for a third time on stage 12's 203.6km race from Aurillac to Villeneuve-sur-Lot and then carried the green jersey all the way into the finale in Nice to win the points classification.\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2335, \"end\": 2343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aurillac\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.013841467623069e-20, \"text\": \"Aurillac\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aurillac\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aurillac\"}, {\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Villeneuve_XIII_RLLG\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.090747589667211e-22, \"text\": \"Villeneuve-sur-Lot\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Villeneuve_XIII_RLLG\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Villeneuve_XIII_RLLG\"}, {\"begin\": 2387, \"end\": 2399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Points_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.408491209014809e-64, \"text\": \"green jersey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Points_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Points_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2431, \"end\": 2435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.739628163605791e-14, \"text\": \"Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The victory in Torino is one of many highlights for Girmay during his career, his name hit the headlines in 2021 when he took silver in the under-23 race at the Leuven Worlds, then again the following year as he took victories at Gent-Wevelgem and on stage 10 into Jesi at the Giro d'Italia.\", \"from\": 2471, \"to\": 2762, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2486, \"end\": 2492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\", \"score\": 0.9999999999636202, \"rank\": 3.662218629828849e-11, \"text\": \"Torino\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\"}, {\"begin\": 2701, \"end\": 2714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gent\\u2013Wevelgem\", \"score\": 0.9552661580602686, \"rank\": 0.025687336945627005, \"text\": \"Gent-Wevelgem\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gent\\u2013Wevelgem\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gent\\u2013Wevelgem\"}, {\"begin\": 2736, \"end\": 2740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iesi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9507414770002406e-24, \"text\": \"Jesi\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iesi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iesi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Girmay followed in the footsteps of compatriots Natnael Berhane, Merhawi Kudus, and Daniel Teklehaimanot, who became the first Black African to start the Tour de France in 2015 and he stood on the podium as the leader of the polka dot jersey after stage 8 in Le Havre.\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 3032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2812, \"end\": 2827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natnael_Berhane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Natnael Berhane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natnael_Berhane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Natnael_Berhane\"}, {\"begin\": 2829, \"end\": 2842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Merhawi_Kudus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Merhawi Kudus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Merhawi_Kudus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Merhawi_Kudus\"}, {\"begin\": 2848, \"end\": 2868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Teklehaimanot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daniel Teklehaimanot\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Teklehaimanot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Teklehaimanot\"}, {\"begin\": 2891, \"end\": 2904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0722654227359145e-37, \"text\": \"Black African\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2918, \"end\": 2932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.224955562168122e-56, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It means a lot personally for me.\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And especially for the continent because it's been a long time for African Black riders to not win at the Tour de France,\\\" Girmay said after his Tour stage win in Torino.\", \"from\": 3069, \"to\": 3239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3144, \"end\": 3156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazg\\u00fbl\", \"score\": 0.9999993286203315, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Black riders\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazg\\u00fbl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazg\\u00fbl\"}, {\"begin\": 3232, \"end\": 3238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\", \"score\": 0.9999999999636202, \"rank\": 3.662218629828849e-11, \"text\": \"Torino\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It means a lot, especially for Eritrean cycling because we have a long history with cycling.\", \"from\": 3240, \"to\": 3333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3272, \"end\": 3280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eritrea\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6444980733749743e-29, \"text\": \"Eritrean\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eritrea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eritrea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have cycling in our blood and know a lot about the Tour de France so to win today was amazing.\\\"\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3388, \"end\": 3402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.224955562168122e-56, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(KF)      Paris-Roubaix witnessed not one but two rainbow jerseys victories at this season's editions, asLotte Kopecky claimed the Paris-Roubaix Femmestitle for the first time, while Mathieu van der Poel made itback-to-back wins at the Hell of the North.\", \"from\": 3433, \"to\": 3687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3443, \"end\": 3456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"score\": 0.9816675037644488, \"rank\": 0.004431782209564152, \"text\": \"Paris-Roubaix\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\"}, {\"begin\": 3564, \"end\": 3577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"score\": 0.9824390445527784, \"rank\": 0.004431782209564152, \"text\": \"Paris-Roubaix\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\"}, {\"begin\": 3616, \"end\": 3636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mathieu van der Poel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\"}, {\"begin\": 3616, \"end\": 3636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mathieu van der Poel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 'curse of the rainbow jersey' was nowhere to be seen in northern France on the first weekend of April as both Lotte Kopecky and Mathieu van der Poel avoided punctures and crashes to raise their arms in sheer euphoria at the iconic Roubaix Velodrome, albeit achieving the feat in contrasting styles.\", \"from\": 3689, \"to\": 3991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3758, \"end\": 3764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999994597601, \"rank\": 5.383128365799838e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3803, \"end\": 3816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotte_Kopecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lotte Kopecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotte_Kopecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotte_Kopecky\"}, {\"begin\": 3821, \"end\": 3841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mathieu van der Poel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\"}, {\"begin\": 3821, \"end\": 3841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mathieu van der Poel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a race that yo-yoed back and forth with attacks, until a select group of riders, including Kopecky, Elisa Balsamo, Marianne Vos and Pfeiffer Georgi, burst clear with a handful of pav\\u00e9 sectors remaining.\", \"from\": 3993, \"to\": 4202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4100, \"end\": 4113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elisa_Balsamo_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9999999306164706, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elisa Balsamo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elisa_Balsamo_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elisa_Balsamo_(cyclist)\"}, {\"begin\": 4115, \"end\": 4127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marianne Vos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\"}, {\"begin\": 4132, \"end\": 4147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\", \"score\": 0.9999994495557681, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pfeiffer Georgi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Six riders arrived at the velodrome, and Kopecky was the last to launch her sprint.\", \"from\": 4204, \"to\": 4287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Belgian - resplendent in an all-white rainbow kit - timed her sprint to perfection, navigating her way around the outside group at the perfect moment to confirm her place as Queen of the Classics.\", \"from\": 4288, \"to\": 4488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4292, \"end\": 4299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.631373160054418e-18, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 4479, \"end\": 4487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.869622157126948e-180, \"text\": \"Classics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just 24 hours later, a week afterclinching a third Tour of Flanders title, Van der Poel delivered an equally powerful display in northern France.\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4628, \"end\": 4634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999994597601, \"rank\": 5.383128365799838e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Kopecky's decisive move came inside the final 100m, the Dutchman made his key attack with 60km to go.\", \"from\": 4637, \"to\": 4744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4699, \"end\": 4707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.547191892537326e-14, \"text\": \"Dutchman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Benefiting from smart teamwork by his teammates Gianni Vermeersch and Jasper Philipsen, he powered away from the rest of the peloton and would not be seen again.\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4793, \"end\": 4810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianni_Vermeersch\", \"score\": 0.9999981433756102, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gianni Vermeersch\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianni_Vermeersch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianni_Vermeersch\"}, {\"begin\": 4815, \"end\": 4831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jasper Philipsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The time difference between MVDP and the second finisher, his teammate Philipsen, would eventually be three minutes, breaking the record for the fastest edition of L'Enfer du Nord in its 128-year history, and becoming the first rider in 11 years to complete the Flanders-Roubaix double.\", \"from\": 4908, \"to\": 5194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5072, \"end\": 5079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henri-Georges_Clouzot's_Inferno\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.833886122155777e-14, \"text\": \"L'Enfer\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henri-Georges_Clouzot's_Inferno\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henri-Georges_Clouzot's_Inferno\"}, {\"begin\": 5083, \"end\": 5087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regionalliga_Nord\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7340701480347436e-13, \"text\": \"Nord\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regionalliga_Nord\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regionalliga_Nord\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(PT)    In what wasone of the most dramatic moments of the season, Kasia Niewiadoma won the 2024 Tour de France holding off runner-up Demi Vollering by four seconds on the final stage 8 atop Alpe d'Huez tosecure the yellow jersey.\", \"from\": 5195, \"to\": 5425, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5386, \"end\": 5397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alpe d'Huez\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\"}, {\"begin\": 5411, \"end\": 5424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0029750650426203e-143, \"text\": \"yellow jersey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Niewiadoma took the overall lead after finishing second on stage 5.\", \"from\": 5427, \"to\": 5494, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the same day, overnight leader Vollering was involved in a mass crash that caused her to lose 1:19.\", \"from\": 5495, \"to\": 5597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although Vollering clawed seconds back on the penultimate stage into Le Grand-Bronand, it was not enough.\", \"from\": 5598, \"to\": 5703, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Vollering tried to gain back the time lost on the final day with an attack on the mid-stage Col du Glandon.\", \"from\": 5705, \"to\": 5812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5797, \"end\": 5811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Col_du_Glandon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Col du Glandon\", \"types\": [\"Q133056\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Col_du_Glandon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Col_du_Glandon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the race up the 21 hairpins of Alpe d'Huez, Vollering and Pauliena Rooijakkers played a tactical battle for the stage victory.\", \"from\": 5813, \"to\": 5942, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5847, \"end\": 5858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alpe d'Huez\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end, Vollering crossed the line with the win, securing a 10-second bonus seconds toward the overall.\", \"from\": 5944, \"to\": 6051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She also made history as the first woman to have her name etched on a bend of the fabled ascent after winning on Alpe d'Huez.\", \"from\": 6052, \"to\": 6177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6165, \"end\": 6176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alpe d'Huez\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But with the clock still ticking in the race for the general classification, Niewiadoma desperately tried to make it to the finish line with enough time on Vollering to keep the yellow jersey, and she did so by just four seconds.\", \"from\": 6179, \"to\": 6408, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a significant moment in cycling that marked thesmallest margin of victory in the women's or men's Tour de France history, as Greg LeMond beat Laurent Fignon by eight seconds to win the 1989 Tour de France.\", \"from\": 6410, \"to\": 6622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6542, \"end\": 6553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_LeMond\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Greg LeMond\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_LeMond\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_LeMond\"}, {\"begin\": 6607, \"end\": 6621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.224955562168122e-56, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, for Niewiadoma, it signified another turning point in her professional cycling career after having won the world title at the Gravel World Championships last October and secured the win at La Fl\\u00e8che Wallonne atop the Mud de Huy in April.\", \"from\": 6624, \"to\": 6874, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(KF)    Stage four of Itzulia Basque Country might not have been witness to any record-breakingperformanceor an emphatic victory buta mass high-speed crash with 35km remainingarguably had equal impact, shaping the course of several riders' summers and the continuing discourse surrounding rider safety.\", \"from\": 6875, \"to\": 7177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Remco Evenepoel, Jonas Vingegaard, and Primo\\u017e Rogli\\u010d were among the 11 riders forced to quit the race following the incident as the race came around a bend on their way to the day's finish in Legutio.\", \"from\": 7179, \"to\": 7379, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7179, \"end\": 7194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\"}, {\"begin\": 7196, \"end\": 7212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonas_Vingegaard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jonas Vingegaard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonas_Vingegaard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonas_Vingegaard\"}, {\"begin\": 7218, \"end\": 7231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Primo\\u017e_Rogli\\u010d\", \"score\": 0.9999999991196091, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Primo\\u017e Rogli\\u010d\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Primo\\u017e_Rogli\\u010d\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Primo\\u017e_Rogli\\u010d\"}, {\"begin\": 7371, \"end\": 7378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Legutio\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Legutio\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Legutio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Legutio\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rogli\\u010d came away fairly unscathed and would return to racing at theCrit\\u00e9rium du Dauphin\\u00e9, which he would go on to win.\", \"from\": 7380, \"to\": 7498, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Evenepoel suffered a broken collarbone and sustained fractures to his clavicle and scapula when he skidded off the road.\", \"from\": 7500, \"to\": 7631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Soudal Quick-Step rider also managed to make it back for the pre-Tour warm-up race but was off the pace when the race went uphill.\", \"from\": 7632, \"to\": 7766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it was Vingegaard who was the worst affected by the crash,suffering a collapsed lung alongside broken ribs and collarbone.\", \"from\": 7768, \"to\": 7899, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Dane would not return to action until the Grand D\\u00e8part for the Tour de France at the end of June, almost three months after the incident.\", \"from\": 7900, \"to\": 8041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7967, \"end\": 7981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.224955562168122e-56, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps it's a testament to his recovery that he challenged Poga\\u010dar as well as he did en route to second place overall.\", \"from\": 8043, \"to\": 8162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8103, \"end\": 8110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"score\": 0.9956688528450125, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Poga\\u010dar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The crash wasn't the first of note to occur during the Spring either, with Wout van Aert among the abandons followinga nasty crash in the bunch at Dwars door Vlaanderen.\", \"from\": 8164, \"to\": 8333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8239, \"end\": 8252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wout van Aert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\"}, {\"begin\": 8311, \"end\": 8332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0450373895463388e-44, \"text\": \"Dwars door Vlaanderen\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\"}, {\"begin\": 8311, \"end\": 8332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0450373895463388e-44, \"text\": \"Dwars door Vlaanderen\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's led to rider safety being a hot topic this season, with theUCI trialling a variety of measures to reduce safety risksincluding a 'yellow card' system and subtle changes to the 3km rule.\", \"from\": 8334, \"to\": 8524, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(PT)    Racing at his 15thTour de Francein July,Mark Cavendishbroke the all-time stage win record set by Eddy Merckx by securing his 35th stage victory at the French Grand Tour on stage 5 in Saint Vulbas, the latest step in his own era in the history of sprinting.\", \"from\": 8525, \"to\": 8789, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8630, \"end\": 8641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.288151215867551e-165, \"text\": \"Eddy Merckx\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cavendish had announced his retirement the previous season but reneged on the idea after he crashed out of the 2023 Tour de France and lost his chance to establish a new record, that he had shared with Merckx, both on 34 - and a record that had stood for 48 years.\", \"from\": 8791, \"to\": 9055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8791, \"end\": 8800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\", \"score\": 0.7185841663703676, \"rank\": 0.391625429491196, \"text\": \"Cavendish\", \"types\": [\"Q756\", \"Q4886\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\"}, {\"begin\": 8907, \"end\": 8921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.224955562168122e-56, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 8993, \"end\": 8999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.730263310432501e-126, \"text\": \"Merckx\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While racing for Astana-Qazaqstan on stage 5 at the 2024 Tour de France, Cavendish hit the front from distance to claim the win, beating Jasper Philipsen (Alpecin-Deceuninck) and Alexander Kristoff (Uno-X Mobility).\", \"from\": 9057, \"to\": 9272, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9130, \"end\": 9139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\", \"score\": 0.7185841663703676, \"rank\": 0.391625429491196, \"text\": \"Cavendish\", \"types\": [\"Q756\", \"Q4886\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\"}, {\"begin\": 9194, \"end\": 9210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jasper Philipsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\"}, {\"begin\": 9236, \"end\": 9254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_Kristoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexander Kristoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_Kristoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_Kristoff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All of\\u00a0Cavendish's Tour de France stage wins\\u00a0have come in bunch sprints.\", \"from\": 9274, \"to\": 9346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9281, \"end\": 9290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\", \"score\": 0.7185841663703676, \"rank\": 0.391625429491196, \"text\": \"Cavendish\", \"types\": [\"Q756\", \"Q4886\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His first four wins were with Columbia in 2008, then his next 16 with HTC and their famed lead-out train from 2008 through 2011.\", \"from\": 9347, \"to\": 9475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He also took three stage wins while racing for Team Sky in 2012, and another three with QuickStep between 2013 and 2015.\", \"from\": 9476, \"to\": 9596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9523, \"end\": 9531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Team Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ineos_Grenadiers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He went on to race Dimension Data, where he won four stages in the 2016 edition, before his resurgent stint with Deceuninck-Quickstep in 2021 when he won another four stages.\", \"from\": 9598, \"to\": 9772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9617, \"end\": 9631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_Qhubeka_NextHash\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.25032247174145e-32, \"text\": \"Dimension Data\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_Qhubeka_NextHash\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_Qhubeka_NextHash\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A prolonged career with Astana-Qazaqstan into 2024 saw him finally secure his record-breaking 35th Tour stage win.\", \"from\": 9773, \"to\": 9887, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cyclingnewslooked back on every one of Cavendish's 35 Tour de France victoriesthat make him the event's greatest-ever sprinter.\", \"from\": 9889, \"to\": 10016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9928, \"end\": 9937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\", \"score\": 0.7185841663703676, \"rank\": 0.391625429491196, \"text\": \"Cavendish\", \"types\": [\"Q756\", \"Q4886\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cavendish_banana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(KF)      Remco Evenepoel and Kristen Faulkner both starred at the Olympic Games this summer, clinching two gold medals each across their respective disciplines.\", \"from\": 10017, \"to\": 10178, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10047, \"end\": 10063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristen_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999993389976591, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kristen Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristen_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristen_Faulkner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In dreary and wet conditions Evenepoel powered to time trial victory on the first weekend of the Games - putting 15 seconds intoFilippo Ganna's time despite the treacherous conditions on the French capital's roads.\", \"from\": 10180, \"to\": 10394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10371, \"end\": 10377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.79861129521661e-13, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Evenepoel could not hide his joy as he crossed the line, already aware his time was enough for gold, punching the air as headded yet another major TT title to his record.\", \"from\": 10395, \"to\": 10565, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10542, \"end\": 10544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.479557488839434e-11, \"text\": \"TT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A week later though, tothe backdrop of Montmartre's cobbled streets packed with fans, the Belgian truly wrote his name into Olympic history.\", \"from\": 10567, \"to\": 10707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10606, \"end\": 10616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.103225254916115e-32, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}, {\"begin\": 10657, \"end\": 10664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.631373160054418e-18, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coming to the fore with 40km of the 272km race remaining, Evenepoel ignited the afterburners to power through the remnants of the day's early break and lead the race with only Valentin Madouas remaining by his side at the 15km to-go marker.\", \"from\": 10709, \"to\": 10949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10885, \"end\": 10901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valentin Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Frenchman was duly dropped on the final ascent through Montmartre, but Evenepoel - seemingly untouchable - could not foresee a mechanical nearly deriding his golden double dream.\", \"from\": 10951, \"to\": 11133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11010, \"end\": 11020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.103225254916115e-32, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A frantic minute ensued, with the Belgian gesturing and shouting to his mechanic for a new bike.\", \"from\": 11135, \"to\": 11231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11169, \"end\": 11176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.631373160054418e-18, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The handover proved slick and the crisis averted.\", \"from\": 11232, \"to\": 11281, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He arrived at the finish line with time to spare.\", \"from\": 11283, \"to\": 11332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In so doing he becamethe first male rider to secure both road and time trial titles in the same Olympics- posing for a finish line photo that will ensure in cycling history.\", \"from\": 11333, \"to\": 11506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In vast contrast, Kristen Faulkner was by no means a favourite for the women's road race - in fact, she wasn't even on the startlist until a last-minute switch.\", \"from\": 11508, \"to\": 11668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11526, \"end\": 11542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristen_Faulkner\", \"score\": 0.9999993389976591, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kristen Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristen_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kristen_Faulkner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps it was her rank outsider status that saw none of Marianne Vos, Lotte \\u00a0Kopecky, or Kata Blanka Vas respond to her attack with 3km remaining.\", \"from\": 11670, \"to\": 11817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11727, \"end\": 11739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marianne Vos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\"}, {\"begin\": 11760, \"end\": 11775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanka_Vas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kata Blanka Vas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanka_Vas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanka_Vas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They'd quickly regret that when the American powered across the line over a minute ahead of themto win the women's road race- too focused on the Olympic title to even sit up and celebrate.\", \"from\": 11819, \"to\": 12007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Faulkner would equal Evenepoel's golden exploits three days later, helpingTeam USA to win their first-ever gold medal in the women's Team Pursuitas they led from start to finish to see off New Zealand.\", \"from\": 12009, \"to\": 12210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12009, \"end\": 12017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.235690526919375e-29, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}, {\"begin\": 12198, \"end\": 12209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999507846838545, \"rank\": 4.921681128817396e-05, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(PT)    Demi Volleringwent into the 2024 Tour de France Femmes as the out-right favourite to win a second consecutive overall title after she had an outstanding early season that saw her on a stage racing winning streak at La Vuelta Feminine, Itzulia Women, Vuelta a Burgos and Tour de Suisse.\", \"from\": 12211, \"to\": 12504, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12252, \"end\": 12266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.224955562168122e-56, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 12434, \"end\": 12443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vuelta_a_Espa\\u00f1a\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Vuelta\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vuelta_a_Espa\\u00f1a\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vuelta_a_Espa\\u00f1a\"}, {\"begin\": 12454, \"end\": 12467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzulia_Women\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.934568331339274e-20, \"text\": \"Itzulia Women\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzulia_Women\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzulia_Women\"}, {\"begin\": 12478, \"end\": 12484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burgos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.573085022412174e-27, \"text\": \"Burgos\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burgos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Burgos\"}, {\"begin\": 12489, \"end\": 12503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Suisse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.385205210275186e-31, \"text\": \"Tour de Suisse\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Suisse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Suisse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She had also opted not to compete at the Giro d'Italia Women in order to focus on the Tour, which had moved to a new August date to accommodate the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 12505, \"to\": 12667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12546, \"end\": 12559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.392785368895284e-50, \"text\": \"Giro d'Italia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She looked well on her way to achieving that goal when she took a surprise win in the stage 3 time trial and moved into yellow in Rotterdam and then extended that lead into Li\\u00e8ge the following day.\", \"from\": 12669, \"to\": 12866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12799, \"end\": 12808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rotterdam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.988127575403196e-28, \"text\": \"Rotterdam\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rotterdam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rotterdam\"}, {\"begin\": 12842, \"end\": 12847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\", \"score\": 0.9918545502535505, \"rank\": 0.005035105293386595, \"text\": \"Li\\u00e8ge\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adevastating crash on the exit of a roundaboutsaw Vollering crash hard with 6.3km to go on stage 5 into Amn\\u00e9ville, and she was unable to remount her bike for 49 seconds as she clutched at the back of her left leg with what appeared to be a hip injury, slowly getting back on her bike to make her way to the finish, initially alone and without support from SD Worx-Protime.\", \"from\": 12868, \"to\": 13240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12972, \"end\": 12981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amn\\u00e9ville\", \"score\": 0.8070032079679424, \"rank\": 0.20242214532867547, \"text\": \"Amn\\u00e9ville\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amn\\u00e9ville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amn\\u00e9ville\"}, {\"begin\": 13224, \"end\": 13226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Diego_Padres\", \"score\": 0.9999802817781096, \"rank\": 1.970733916904378e-05, \"text\": \"SD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Diego_Padres\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Diego_Padres\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The overall classification completely flipped on its head when Vollering crossed the line 1:47 behind her teammate and stage winner Blanka Vas, but more importantly, she had also lost 1:19 to Kasia Niewiadoma (Canyon-SRAM) heading into the final three stages.\", \"from\": 13242, \"to\": 13501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13374, \"end\": 13384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanka_Vas\", \"score\": 0.9999999946303433, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Blanka Vas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanka_Vas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanka_Vas\"}, {\"begin\": 13434, \"end\": 13450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katarzyna_Niewiadoma\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kasia Niewiadoma\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katarzyna_Niewiadoma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katarzyna_Niewiadoma\"}, {\"begin\": 13452, \"end\": 13463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canyon\\u2013SRAM\", \"score\": 0.9294047605330832, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canyon-SRAM\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canyon\\u2013SRAM\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canyon\\u2013SRAM\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Questions swirled around the SD Worx-Protime's tactics and why their yellow jersey was left isolated in the closing kilometres of this stage, but her teammates and the riders from rival teams who had split off the front said they did not realize Vollering was involved in the crash, but that there was little that could be done with such a short distance to the finish line.\", \"from\": 13503, \"to\": 13877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13572, \"end\": 13585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0029750650426203e-143, \"text\": \"yellow jersey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vollering said she was 'empty, sour but proud' after capturing the finale stage 8 victory on Alpe d'Huez, but having also lost the overall race by just four seconds to Niewaidoma.\", \"from\": 13879, \"to\": 14058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13972, \"end\": 13983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alpe d'Huez\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alpe_d'Huez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although SD Worx-Protime went into the Tour de France in full support of Vollering, there had already been tensions between them surrounding rumours of her departure at the end of the 2024 season.\", \"from\": 14060, \"to\": 14256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14099, \"end\": 14113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.224955562168122e-56, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It later emerged thatVollering had signed a contract at the end of the spring to compete with FDJ-SUEZ from 2025 to 2026, where she will once again target a victory at the2025 Tour de France Femmes.\", \"from\": 14257, \"to\": 14455, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(KF)    The opening week of La Vuelta a Espa\\u00f1a looked to be falling perfectly into place for Red Bull-Bora-Hansgrohe when Primo\\u017e Rogli\\u010d - returning to racing after abandoning the Tour de France - took the red jersey on stage four.\", \"from\": 14456, \"to\": 14686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14484, \"end\": 14493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vuelta_a_Espa\\u00f1a\", \"score\": 0.9999999981737346, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Vuelta\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vuelta_a_Espa\\u00f1a\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vuelta_a_Espa\\u00f1a\"}, {\"begin\": 14635, \"end\": 14649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.224955562168122e-56, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That was until, in their directeur sportif Patxi Vila's words,\\\"things got out of hand.\\\"\", \"from\": 14687, \"to\": 14774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14730, \"end\": 14740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patxi_Vila\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Patxi Vila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patxi_Vila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patxi_Vila\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Things' specifically being Ben O'Connor, with the Australian putting six minutes into GC rivals on stage six after soloing to victory from the break.\", \"from\": 14776, \"to\": 14926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 14804, \"end\": 14816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_O'Connor_(hurler)\", \"score\": 0.910513111011931, \"rank\": 0.08169533169529136, \"text\": \"Ben O'Connor\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_O'Connor_(hurler)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_O'Connor_(hurler)\"}, {\"begin\": 14827, \"end\": 14837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999633328123, \"rank\": 2.3914090127359418e-08, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 14863, \"end\": 14865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.183179382697026e-46, \"text\": \"GC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_classification_in_the_Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When we think about race favourites lending out the jersey to outsiders for a few days to alleviate pressure, this wasn't it.\", \"from\": 14927, \"to\": 15052, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian and his Decathlon AG2R La Mondiale team defended the jersey impressively.\", \"from\": 15053, \"to\": 15141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15053, \"end\": 15067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.476193580898389e-52, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 15086, \"end\": 15102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AG2R_La_Mondiale\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"AG2R La Mondiale\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AG2R_La_Mondiale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/AG2R_La_Mondiale\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately though, after 13 days on O'Connor's back, the race leader's jersey was wrestled back into Rogli\\u010d's control on the Alto de Moncalvillo - with the Slovenian all but sealing his record-equalling fourth Vuelta title in the process.\", \"from\": 15143, \"to\": 15381, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15244, \"end\": 15250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Primo\\u017e_Rogli\\u010d\", \"score\": 0.9961576053832583, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rogli\\u010d\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Primo\\u017e_Rogli\\u010d\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Primo\\u017e_Rogli\\u010d\"}, {\"begin\": 15299, \"end\": 15308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\", \"score\": 0.999996282832941, \"rank\": 3.7171814925949512e-06, \"text\": \"Slovenian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nonetheless,O'Connor held on for second place, describing the result, which is his best Grand Tour finish and first podium, as \\\"a bit of a dream, I have been close before but to get it now is such an amazing thing.\\\"\", \"from\": 15383, \"to\": 15598, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15471, \"end\": 15481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Tour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.207167636990729e-14, \"text\": \"Grand Tour\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Tour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Tour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three weeks later, he'd add a road race World Championships runner-up spot to his palmar\\u00e8s too, to cap off his best season to date.\", \"from\": 15600, \"to\": 15731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Perth native played his role in the chasing group to perfection, behind an unassailable Tadej Poga\\u010dar.\", \"from\": 15733, \"to\": 15839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15737, \"end\": 15742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0107589044274236e-15, \"text\": \"Perth\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perth\"}, {\"begin\": 15825, \"end\": 15838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"score\": 0.9999999996089173, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tadej Poga\\u010dar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By no means the fastest finisher in the group, he bided his time and let other riders show their hands before bursting away with just a few kilometres remaining, tellingCyclingnewsat the finish line that this result\\\"is for Aussie cycling, not just for me.\", \"from\": 15840, \"to\": 16095, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"(PT)    Marianne Vos has had another outstanding season full of firsts and records, butthe most defining was her first-time victory at Dwars door Vlaanderen, which ticks off a landmark number of 250 career road race victories.\", \"from\": 16095, \"to\": 16322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16104, \"end\": 16116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marianne Vos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Vos\"}, {\"begin\": 16231, \"end\": 16252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0450373895463388e-44, \"text\": \"Dwars door Vlaanderen\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\"}, {\"begin\": 16231, \"end\": 16252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0450373895463388e-44, \"text\": \"Dwars door Vlaanderen\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She had an impressive Classics campaign, which was a clear indication that she was back to her best after late 2023 surgery on her iliac artery, with first-time wins at Omloop Het Nieuwsblad and \\u00a0Dwars door Vlaanderen, along with a victory at Amstel Gold Race.\", \"from\": 16324, \"to\": 16584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16346, \"end\": 16354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.869622157126948e-180, \"text\": \"Classics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Classic_cycle_races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She went on to win two stages and the points classification at La Vuelta Feminine, a stage win and the overall title atVolta Ciclista a Catalunya, and the points classification at the Tour de France Femmes.\", \"from\": 16586, \"to\": 16792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16649, \"end\": 16658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vuelta_a_Espa\\u00f1a\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Vuelta\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vuelta_a_Espa\\u00f1a\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vuelta_a_Espa\\u00f1a\"}, {\"begin\": 16770, \"end\": 16784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.224955562168122e-56, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also secured the silver medal in the road race at the Paris Olympics Games and capped off the season by winning the world title at the UCI Gravel World Championships, adding a 14th rainbow jersey to her extensive collection of titles; eight cyclocross, three road race, two track and one gravel.\", \"from\": 16794, \"to\": 17093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16933, \"end\": 16936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.056421753876695e-14, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}, {\"begin\": 16979, \"end\": 16993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"rainbow jersey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vos has amassed 255 career road race wins by the end of the 2024 season, putting another defining stamp on her GOAT status in professional cycling.\", \"from\": 17095, \"to\": 17242, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a number you do not dare think about at the beginning of your career,\\\" said Vos of her 250th victory at Dwars door Vlaanderen.\", \"from\": 17243, \"to\": 17375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17353, \"end\": 17374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0450373895463388e-44, \"text\": \"Dwars door Vlaanderen\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\"}, {\"begin\": 17353, \"end\": 17374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0450373895463388e-44, \"text\": \"Dwars door Vlaanderen\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Over the years you can make a lot of memories of different highs and lows and then this is definitely a very nice highlight.\\\"\", \"from\": 17376, \"to\": 17502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(KF)    Grace Brown called time on her career as a professional cyclist in scintillating style as she became the first Australian woman to win a Monument at Li\\u00e8ge-Bastogne-Li\\u00e8ge before reaffirming her legendary status by becoming the first woman to win Olympic time trial gold and the World Championships time trial in the same year.\", \"from\": 17503, \"to\": 17836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17504, \"end\": 17506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KF2\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4686550097137875e-22, \"text\": \"KF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KF2\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KF2\"}, {\"begin\": 17511, \"end\": 17522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murder_of_Grace_Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6003078987536837e-23, \"text\": \"Grace Brown\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murder_of_Grace_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Murder_of_Grace_Brown\"}, {\"begin\": 17622, \"end\": 17632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999633328123, \"rank\": 2.3914090127359418e-08, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 17660, \"end\": 17680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\\u2013Bastogne\\u2013Li\\u00e8ge\", \"score\": 0.9746117254729166, \"rank\": 0.016748768472911003, \"text\": \"Li\\u00e8ge-Bastogne-Li\\u00e8ge\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\\u2013Bastogne\\u2013Li\\u00e8ge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\\u2013Bastogne\\u2013Li\\u00e8ge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brown claimed victory at Li\\u00e8ge when she outsprintedElisa Longo Borghiniand Demi Vollering to the title after spending half of the race in the breakaway.\", \"from\": 17838, \"to\": 17990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17863, \"end\": 17868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\", \"score\": 0.9918545502535505, \"rank\": 0.005035105293386595, \"text\": \"Li\\u00e8ge\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\"}, {\"begin\": 17913, \"end\": 17927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demi_Vollering\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Demi Vollering\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demi_Vollering\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demi_Vollering\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet just two months later, at the age of 31, she announced 2024 would be her last in the women's WorldTour.\", \"from\": 17992, \"to\": 18099, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I really miss my life in Australia with my husband, my family and my friends and it is something that is harder and harder to leave,\\\" she explained whenannouncing her retirement.\", \"from\": 18100, \"to\": 18279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18126, \"end\": 18135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9999483898758469, \"rank\": 5.160851323378957e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That decision appeared to ignite a 'leave it all out there' mentality in the rider from Melbourne for the rest of the season as she stunned the field on the opening weekend of the Paris Olympics,storming the women's time trial eventby over a minute and a half to eventual silver medallist Anna Henderson.\", \"from\": 18281, \"to\": 18585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18369, \"end\": 18378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Storm\", \"score\": 0.9994314290493675, \"rank\": 0.0005688944080663471, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Storm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Storm\"}, {\"begin\": 18570, \"end\": 18584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"score\": 0.9999958972014192, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can be really proud to go out on such a high,\\\" Brown told reporters after her win.\", \"from\": 18587, \"to\": 18672, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet the historic feat in Paris did not mark the peak of the Australian's season - that arrived two months later in Switzerland.\", \"from\": 18673, \"to\": 18800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18698, \"end\": 18703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6119243440588455e-47, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 18733, \"end\": 18743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999633328123, \"rank\": 2.3914090127359418e-08, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 18788, \"end\": 18799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999999003703174, \"rank\": 9.962976830262107e-08, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brown beat Demi Vollering by a matter of 16 seconds inthe elite women's time trial at the World Championships, finally claiming a rainbow jersey after two second places in the event.\", \"from\": 18802, \"to\": 18984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18932, \"end\": 18946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"rainbow jersey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rounding out her career as the first woman to conquer both major TT titles in one year, Brown described it as a \\\"dream\\\" and was \\\"really, really lucky to have the end of my career like this.\", \"from\": 18986, \"to\": 19175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19051, \"end\": 19053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.479557488839434e-11, \"text\": \"TT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's special.\\\"\", \"from\": 19176, \"to\": 19190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(PT)      Italy had to wait a long 16 years until one of their own secured the coveted maglia rosa at the Giro d'Italia Women.\", \"from\": 19191, \"to\": 19317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19201, \"end\": 19206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.1852395114971885e-18, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 19297, \"end\": 19310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.392785368895284e-50, \"text\": \"Giro d'Italia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It finally happened in this year's 35th edition in the most dominating of fashions asElisa Longo Broghini led the eight-day race from start to finishand was crowned the overall winner in L'Aquila.\", \"from\": 19318, \"to\": 19514, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19505, \"end\": 19513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L'Aquila\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.364136186651705e-26, \"text\": \"L'Aquila\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L'Aquila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L'Aquila\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Longo Borghini is the reigning Italian Champion and has competed in 13 editions of the Giro d'Italia Women and finished twice on the podium in 2017 and 2020, and said it took an entire team effort to make that step up as the overall champion.\", \"from\": 19516, \"to\": 19758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19547, \"end\": 19554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.013977728793959e-21, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 19603, \"end\": 19616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.392785368895284e-50, \"text\": \"Giro d'Italia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She pulled on the maglia rosa after the stage 1 time trial in Brescia, and then carryied the race lead through Volta Mantovana, Toano, Urbino, Foligno, Chieti and to the top of the iconic Blockhaus, in what was a dramatic race for time bonuses on the penultimate queen stage 7 against runner-up Lotte Kopecky (SD Worx-Protime).\", \"from\": 19760, \"to\": 20087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19822, \"end\": 19829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brescia\", \"score\": 0.9320170552473797, \"rank\": 0.0729417389623709, \"text\": \"Brescia\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brescia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brescia\"}, {\"begin\": 19871, \"end\": 19886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volta_Mantovana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Volta Mantovana\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volta_Mantovana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volta_Mantovana\"}, {\"begin\": 19888, \"end\": 19893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toano,_Virginia\", \"score\": 0.9087328061873676, \"rank\": 0.05889423076929021, \"text\": \"Toano\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toano,_Virginia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toano,_Virginia\"}, {\"begin\": 19895, \"end\": 19901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Urbino\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.314989676732676e-21, \"text\": \"Urbino\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Urbino\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Urbino\"}, {\"begin\": 19903, \"end\": 19910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foligno\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3154077764956495e-21, \"text\": \"Foligno\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foligno\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foligno\"}, {\"begin\": 19912, \"end\": 19918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chieti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0550586248141976e-21, \"text\": \"Chieti\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chieti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chieti\"}, {\"begin\": 19948, \"end\": 19957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maiella\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1041182508405497e-26, \"text\": \"Blockhaus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maiella\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maiella\"}, {\"begin\": 20055, \"end\": 20068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotte_Kopecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lotte Kopecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotte_Kopecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lotte_Kopecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a dramatic stage 8 finale, she led by just one second ahead of Kopecky in the overall classification.\", \"from\": 20089, \"to\": 20193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A breakaway of three took the top three stage places, and then Longo Borghini accelerated and sprinted out of the field in the last kilometre to claim fourth place on the day and win the overall title by 21 seconds ahead of Kopecky.\", \"from\": 20194, \"to\": 20426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Longo Borghini was the first Italian to win the maglia rosa at the women's race since five-time winner Fabiana Luperini last won the title in 2008, and added her name to a list of compatriots to have won the race that also includes Maria Canins, Roberta Bonanomi, and Michela Fanini.\", \"from\": 20428, \"to\": 20711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20531, \"end\": 20547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fabiana_Luperini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fabiana Luperini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fabiana_Luperini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fabiana_Luperini\"}, {\"begin\": 20660, \"end\": 20672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Canins\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maria Canins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Canins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Canins\"}, {\"begin\": 20674, \"end\": 20690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roberta_Bonanomi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roberta Bonanomi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roberta_Bonanomi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roberta_Bonanomi\"}, {\"begin\": 20696, \"end\": 20703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michela_Pace\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michela\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michela_Pace\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michela_Pace\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(KF)    Tadej Poga\\u010dar delivered the best season of his stellar career so far, becoming just thethird male rider to complete the Triple Crownof Giro d'Italia, Tour de France, and World Championship road race victories in one season.\", \"from\": 20712, \"to\": 20943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20720, \"end\": 20733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"score\": 0.9999999996089173, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tadej Poga\\u010dar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\"}, {\"begin\": 20855, \"end\": 20868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.392785368895284e-50, \"text\": \"Giro d'Italia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\"}, {\"begin\": 20870, \"end\": 20884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.224955562168122e-56, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alongside becoming the third man after Eddy Merckx and Stephen Roche to complete the feat, Poga\\u010daradded a second Li\\u00e8ge-Bastogne-Li\\u00e8ge titleand made itfour consecutive wins at Il Lombardia.\", \"from\": 20945, \"to\": 21133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20984, \"end\": 20995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.288151215867551e-165, \"text\": \"Eddy Merckx\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\"}, {\"begin\": 21000, \"end\": 21013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Roche\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.729936858107853e-143, \"text\": \"Stephen Roche\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Roche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Roche\"}, {\"begin\": 21120, \"end\": 21132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_di_Lombardia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0616074127711772e-96, \"text\": \"Il Lombardia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_di_Lombardia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_di_Lombardia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On his way to claiminghis third maillot jauneanda first maglia rosa, Poga\\u010dar scored six stage wins at the Tour and Giro respectively.\", \"from\": 21135, \"to\": 21268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21204, \"end\": 21211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"score\": 0.9956688528450125, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Poga\\u010dar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet, unquestionably,the Slovenian's World Championships victorywas the most poignant of his successes in 2024, both for how he achieved it and what it meant in the context of cycling's history.\", \"from\": 21270, \"to\": 21463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21294, \"end\": 21303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\", \"score\": 0.999996282832941, \"rank\": 3.7171814925949512e-06, \"text\": \"Slovenian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the reasons Poga\\u010dar is alreadylauded by many as one of the greatest riders to grace the sportis his willingness to tackle races head-on, dictating proceedings on his terms and leaving rivals to guess his next move.\", \"from\": 21465, \"to\": 21686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21484, \"end\": 21491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"score\": 0.9956688528450125, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Poga\\u010dar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nowhere was this clearer than in Switzerland when the 26-year-old launched an attack from the peloton with 100km to go, weaving through the day's breakaway as if they were barely pedalling and then riding solo to the finish from no less than 50km until the line.\", \"from\": 21688, \"to\": 21950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21721, \"end\": 21732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999999003703174, \"rank\": 9.962976830262107e-08, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking during his post-race press conference,Poga\\u010dar confirmed the long-range adventure was by no means planned, and described it as a \\\"stupid attack.\\\"\", \"from\": 21952, \"to\": 22105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21999, \"end\": 22006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"score\": 0.9956688528450125, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Poga\\u010dar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tadej_Poga\\u010dar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A fortnight later the three-time Tour de France winner was at it again - now proudly donning the rainbow jersey - producing a mesmerising 48.4km solo effort to win a fourth consecutive Il Lombardia andhis 25th victory of the campaign.\", \"from\": 22107, \"to\": 22341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22204, \"end\": 22218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"rainbow jersey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\"}, {\"begin\": 22292, \"end\": 22304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_di_Lombardia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0616074127711772e-96, \"text\": \"Il Lombardia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_di_Lombardia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_di_Lombardia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(PT)  Pete joinedCyclingnewsas Engagement Editor in 2024 having previously worked at GCN as a digital content creator, cutting his teeth in cycling journalism across their app, social media platforms, and website.\", \"from\": 22342, \"to\": 22555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22427, \"end\": 22430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GameCube\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.976259765093392e-31, \"text\": \"GCN\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GameCube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GameCube\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While studying Journalism at university, he worked as a freelancer forCycling Weeklyreporting on races such as the Giro d'Italia and Milan-San Remo alongside covering the Women's Super League and non-league football for various titles.\", \"from\": 22556, \"to\": 22791, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22689, \"end\": 22703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Milan\\u2013San_Remo\", \"score\": 0.96375